(10) Conditional Entrant

A noncitizen present in the U.S. as a conditional entrant under section 203(a)(7) of the

INA is an eligible noncitizen when he or she:

(a) has resided as a qualified noncitizen in the U.S. for five years;

(b) was born on or before August 22, 1931 and was lawfully residing in the U.S. on 8/22/96;

(c) is a child under under 18 years of age;

(d) is disabled as defined by 106 CMR 361.210; or

(e) is a veteran or active duty personnel as defined by 106 CMR 362.240(F).

